OL,7,F"To this day, I struggle to understand
OL,8,Fhow she could be persuaded to take
OL,9,Fsuch a course of action.
OL,11,F"She was someone for whom I had the
OL,12,Futmost respect."
OL,14,FMr Wright later said he was proud to
OL,15,Fthink Lady Lawrence considered him a
OL,16,F"professional ally", adding: "I was
OL,17,Fdeeply committed to her campaign and
OL,18,Freferred to her at my office as `Daily
OL,19,FMail royalty'."
